  "prompt": "How long can I stay outside the UK as a dependant of the tier2 visa?",
  "response": "As a dependant of a Tier 2 visa holder in the UK, you can generally stay outside the UK for up to 12 months without affecting your immigration status. If you stay outside the UK for more than 12 months, your dependant visa may be considered invalid, and you may need to apply for a new visa to return to the UK.\n\nIt's important to bear in mind that if you plan to apply for settlement (indefinite leave to remain) in the UK later, exceeding the 12-month absence could affect your eligibility for that application. Always check the most current guidelines and policies from the UK Home Office or consult an immigration advisor for personalized advice.",
